Inspection of Gender

data_cleaned %>%
  group_by(Gender, below_11_years_old) %>% 
  summarise(total = n()) %>% 
  ungroup() %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = Gender, y = total, fill = fct_rev(below_11_years_old)))+
  geom_bar(stat = "identity", position = "dodge", color = "black")+
  theme_bw()+
  labs(fill = "Below 11 \nYears Old",
       title = "Amount of Students Below 11 Years Old Reading Age")

Inspection of Primary Schools

Origin School

total_data %>% 
  group_by(Origin_School, below_11_years_old) %>% 
  summarise(value = n()) %>%
  ungroup() %>%
  group_by(Origin_School) %>% 
  mutate(percent = value/sum(value),
         total_school_amount = sum(value)) %>% 
  ungroup() %>%
  mutate(Origin_School = ifelse(total_school_amount<3, "Small Schools", Origin_School)) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = fct_reorder(Origin_School, -value, .fun = sum), y = value, fill = fct_rev(below_11_years_old)))+ 
  geom_bar(stat = "identity")+
  theme_bw()+
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle=60, hjust=1))+
  scale_y_continuous(name="Frequency", limits=c(0, 60), breaks = seq(0,60,5))+
  labs(fill = "Below Reading\nAge",
       x = "Primary School",
       title = "Distribution of Students Below a 11 Year Old Reading Age")

Inspection of Indigenous Status

Absolute Value

total_data_2 %>% 
  group_by(indigenous, below_11_years_old) %>% 
  summarise(value = n()) %>%
  ungroup() %>%
  group_by(indigenous) %>% 
  mutate(percent = value/sum(value),
         total_school_amount = sum(value)) %>% 
  ungroup() %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = indigenous, y = value, fill = fct_rev(below_11_years_old)))+
  geom_bar(stat = "identity", position = "stack", color = "black")+
  scale_y_continuous(name="Frequency", limits=c(0, 130), breaks = seq(0,130,10))+
  theme_bw()+
  labs(fill = "Below Reading\nAge",
       x = "Indigenous Status",
       title = "Absolute Value of Students Below a 11 Year Old Reading Age", 
       subtitle = "Indigenous Status")
